			<h6>Kruncher said:</h6>
		</div>
		<div class="span-11" style="margin-left: 160px;">
			
			<p>Ever struggle designing a complicated form on a worksheet? You&#39;re merging cells, setting row and column widths, that kind of thing. You&#39;re trying to put something somewhere specific, but if you change widths or heights, something else won&#39;t appear the way you want it to. Arrgh!</p>

<p>That&#39;s the time to pull out the camera tool. Put what you want to display on a different sheet, format it exactly as you want. Easy, now that you won&#39;t have to fight with anything else. Now that bit looks good: good formatting, widths, heights, etc.</p>

<p>Now take a picture of it and put the picture on the main form page. Size and position the object precisely as you need. Simple and elegant.</p>
		</div>
		</div>
	

			
	
		
		


