<br/>
	
	
		<div class="span-15 comment" style="clear: both; margin: 0; padding: 0;">
		<div class="span-4 left" style="border-right: 1px solid #038A3E; min-height: 50px">
			<span class="comment-date">September 16, 2006</span><br/>
			<h6>Steve Blevins said:</h6>
		</div>
		<div class="span-11" style="margin-left: 160px;">
			
			<p>Use the U+2588 character in Time New Roman character set.</p>

<p>Run CMD charmap choose Times New Roman scroll 3/4 way down, choose U+2588 Full Block Character, Copy, Paste this into the cell, make sure it is formatted as Times New Roman, and the in cell bar looks more solid. It works with conditional formatting as well.</p>
		</div>
		</div>
	

			
	
		
		


<br/>
	
	
		<div class="span-15 comment" style="clear: both; margin: 0; padding: 0;">
		<div class="span-4 left" style="border-right: 1px solid #038A3E; min-height: 50px">
			<span class="comment-date">September 18, 2006</span><br/>
			<h6>Mark Aylward said:</h6>
		</div>
