		<div class="span-11" style="margin-left: 160px;">
			
			<p>You can convert the bars into columns using Excel&#39;s often forgotten Camera tool - in Excel 2003 you&#39;ll find it in in Customize under Tools.</p>

<p>Build the bars as in the example spreadsheet then simply highlight them, click the camera and paste the resultant picture. The picture will update as the data changes but can be rotated or scaled as necessary.</p>
		</div>
		</div>
	

			
	
		
		


